text.section:
Subsection (2)(c) of this section shall not render null, void, and unenforceable a contract provision that:
Permits a contractor or subcontractor to recover that portion of delay costs caused by acts or omissions of the contracting entity;
Requires notice of any delay by the party affected by the delay;
Provides for reasonable liquidated damages;
Provides for arbitration or any other procedure designed to resolve contract disputes; or
Specifies which costs are recoverable by a contractor or subcontractor for delay.
